data_source_comments: [CWW] from 06:46-07:34 seeing multiple whales, number uncertain. By 07:34 slowly moving southbound (Thomas McKane)
[Orca Network] Biggs T65A5 Indy  may now be angling NW direction  (Rachel Haight)
[Orca Network] Biggs T65A5 Indy hugging shore continuing northbound (Rachel Haight)
[Orca Network] Biggs T65A5 Indy. NW hugging shore (Jennifer Fulton Carpenter)
[Orca Network] Biggs T65A5 Indy now on his own. Northbound hugging shore (Rachel Haight)
[Orca Network] Probably Biggs members of the T65As, but only saw spouts, two of them. (Kit Turner)
[Orca Network] at least 2 grays headed east in Saratoga passage nearing Camano Head. They are mid-channel. (Luanne Seymour)

[Orca Network] Biggs, at least two members of T65As continue northbound close to Whidbey. Others likely across. 
(Sandra Pollard)
[Orca network] Biggs, T65As spread with T65A3 and T65A4 or A5 northbound (Rachel Haight)
[Orca Network] Biggs, T65As, T65A3 and A4 or 5 approaching bush point northbound (Rachel Haight)
[Orca Network] T65As, spread out, T65A3 and T65A5 pushing offshore, northbound, others likely on kitsap side (Rachel Haight)
[Orca Network] Biggs, likely T65As, spread out, moving west fast (Rachel Haight)
[Orca Network] Biggs, spread out across channel. Some off Maxwelton (Rachel Haight)

[Orca Network] Biggs, 4 members of the T65As (T65A, T65A2, T65A4, T65A6) Northbound... standing on shore and there were 4 of them about 20-30 feet out straight in front of the lighthouse! (Julia Nelson)
